works.description: Animal lovers, especially the uber-rich kind, have brought various examples into their homes such as the purchase of the Giant Groth Skeleton or the giant T-Rex garden sculpture. But taking a step further is the $350,000 life-like Triceratops, which one can use to surprise, and perhaps even scare visitors with its ultra-realistic multiple functions. This animal from the past can spot onlookers, snarl at them, stomp its feet, open and close its mouth along with a number of other functions like moving its tri-horned head, but baring the consumption of a human being alive!
